  carbohydrates: 85 g
  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 36 g
  fiber: 6 g
  sodium: 1480 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/stovetop-mac-n-cheese-5a8f0def30006c2e6c06c4d2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a #large pot{} of salted water to a boil. Trim, then
thinly slice @scallions{4}(thinly sliced), separating greens and whites. Cut any
large @broccoli florets{16%ounce} into bite-sized pieces, then place in a #large
microwave-safe bowl{} with a big splash of water. Cover with #plastic wrap{}; poke a
few holes in wrap.

Once water is boiling, add @fusilli pasta{12%ounce} to #pot{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Scoop out and reserve ½ cup pasta
cooking water, then drain thoroughly.

Add @pancetta{8%ounce} to a #large pan{} and place over medium-high heat. Cook,
stirring often, until almost crisp, ~{5-7%minutes}. Add scallion whites and cook until
softened, about ~{1%minute} more. Remove both ingredients from pan with a
#slotted spoon{}, keeping as much oil in pan as possible.

Microwave broccoli in #bowl{} on high heat until tender, about ~{5%minutes}
(microwaves vary). Drain thoroughly. Meanwhile, melt @butter{2%tablespoon} in pan
used for pancetta over medium heat. Add @flour{2%tablespoon} and stir constantly until
it loses its raw smell, about ~{2%minutes}. Slowly pour in @milk{13.5%ounce}, whisking
to combine.

Stir @chicken stock concentrate{2} and ¼ cup pasta cooking water into pan. Let sauce
simmer until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and stir in
@cream cheese{1%ounce} and @Italian cheese blend{1%cup}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} and set aside. Place fusilli, pancetta mixture, broccoli, and
@butter{1%tablespoon} in #pot{} used to cook pasta. Add sauce, stirring to coat.

Return pot to low heat. Stir fusilli mixture until warmed through and butter melts,
~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates and sprinkle with
@Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup} and reserved scallion greens.

> TIP: Add more pasta cooking water if sauce seems dry.